<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="249" height="26" alt="" style="margin-left:26.2pt; margin-top:23.2pt; position:absolute; z-index:-65536" /><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:20pt; font-weight:bold">EIS 32</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The Financial Conduct Authority (FCA)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">was established on 1 April 2013 and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is one of two successor bodies, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">along with the Prudential Regulation Authority (PRA),</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to the Financial Services Authority</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">(FSA).</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">This submission covers:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The FCA’s role and remit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">with particular emphasis on our role</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">overseeing issuers of shares</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and other securities trading in financial </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">markets. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Our responses to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">questions</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">4, 5 and 9</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">in the Committee's call for evidence.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><br /><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Role of the FCA</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">he </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">FCA</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> regulates financial services and markets in the UK. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Our remit is broad. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We are responsible for regulating the conduct of around 26,000</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">financial firms and the prudential</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">regulation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">of around 23,000 not covered by the PRA. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Specifically relevant to the C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ommittee's inquiry, we also regulate some important parts of the UK market infrastructure and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">we are the UK’s listing authority. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">In our role as the listing authority,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">we</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">oversee the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">issue</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">securities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">trad</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">n financial markets. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">call</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> activity "</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">primary market regulation".</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">It is important to note that we do not regulate or supervise issuers themselves, in contrast to financial firms. Rather, our oversight is of the securities issuance process, and how issuers subsequently ensure that sufficient an</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">d accurate information</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> made available to investors</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> to enable them to assess the prospects of the issuer and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">exercise their rights as a holder of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">its </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">securities.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Much</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">of the UK's primary markets</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">regulation is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">based on</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">EU</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">law.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Three directives</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">are</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">pa</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">rticularly important for securities admitted to trading on a regulated market:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Prospectus Directive (PD), which specifies the content and format of the document which</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">issuers must use to make offers of securities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to the public</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">across the EU and/or</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">app</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ly for</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">admission to trading</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Transparency Directive</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">(TD), which harmonised financial reporting across the EU</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">using International Financial</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Reporting</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Standards</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and provided common EU</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">rules requiring the disclosure of major shareholdings in companies;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Market Abuse Directive</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">(MAD), which provided common anti-market abuse rules. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">MAD</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">includes</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">provisions impacting issuers of securities, requiring (among other things) the timely announcement of price sensitive information.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">European law</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">still</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">allow</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">member</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">states</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">retain a domestic listing regime on top of this core of EU regulation.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">In the UK, this is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">set out in the FCA Listing Rules. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The UK listing regime is organised around the Official List, a register of approximately 20,000 securities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">issue</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">d by</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">around</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">2,400</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">issuers.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> There are two categories.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">‘Standard listing’</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the category of the listing regime</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">which</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is based on, and does not add significantly to,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the core European directive-imposed obligations.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Most standard listed securities are bonds</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and other non-equity instruments, although it is open to UK and overseas equity issuers.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">‘Premium listing’</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is only open to equity issuers (both UK and overseas). It has</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">additional</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">specific</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">admission criteria,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a requirement to appoint a sponsor to condu</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ct due diligence,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and obligations to seek shareholder approval for certain transactions.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">These obligations are over and above the minimum level of regulation we are required to impose by EU law.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We summarise the key features of the premium listing regime i</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">n Appendix I.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.11pt; padding-left:7.19pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The UK listing regime, and in particular the premium listing regime, enjoys strong support,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">particularly from buy-side institutional investors </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">(for example pension funds, insurance companies</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, fund managers) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">in the UK. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">believe</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">this</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">enhances</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">confidence in</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">our</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">markets, which is ultimately</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to the benefit of both investors and issuers alike.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">What the listing regime cannot do, however, is take away investment risk. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Nor does it take away shareholders’ responsibilities to inf</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">orm themselves properly before taking an investment decision and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">participate in their company and hold management to account for its decisions. Our review of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">an application for listing focuses on ensuring the applicant meets the admission criteria and i</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s therefore</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">eligible</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">for listing. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We do not consider whether it is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">suitable</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">for listing: so for example, we take no view on the appropriateness of an issuer's business model, nor whether it might be</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the sort of company that we would like investors to have</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> the opportunity to invest</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">in. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Similarly, in our engagement with existing listed companies, we do not challenge the merits of any particular commercial proposal or course of action; rather, we consider when such a proposal needs shareholder approval, disc</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">losure to the market in a particular form, or some other regulatory process designed to keep investors informed and able to exercise their rights.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">As well as listed or "main" markets, issuers can also use "junior", </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">or </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">non-listed markets, of which the Lond</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">on Stock Exchange’s AIM market is by far the largest. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">AIM</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is an exchange-regulated market</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and as suc</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">h it</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> overall operation is encompassed by our regulation of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the London Stock Exchange as a ‘recognised investment exchange’ under FSMA 2000. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The FCA does</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> not directly regulate the primary markets aspects of the AIM market, except where an AIM-quoted issuer makes a public offer of securities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  In these instances,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the prospectus directive applies</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the FCA</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">will review and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">approve the prospectus.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The UK has</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> designated AIM a ‘prescribed market’, meaning trading in AIM-quoted securities is covered by anti-market abuse legislation and the FCA’s Code of Market Conduct.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The FCA’s primary markets regime forms only one part of the regulatory framework that appli</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">es to companies.  Other important elements include the Companies Act or local company law, and the UK Code of Corporate Governance</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. The FCA does not make the Code</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">which </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is the responsibility of the Financial Reporting Council (FRC). The Code is a best practice code addressing a number of topics relating to good board practice: leadership, effectiveness, accountability, remuneration and shareholder relations.  It works thr</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ough the requirement that companies within its scope </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">should</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> ‘comply or </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">explain’. The FCA supports the FRC in this approach through the inclusion in the FCA Listing Rules of the requirement to ‘comply or explain’ in relation to the Code</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Extractive compa</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">nies can be found on all segments of UK markets - primary listed, standard listed and AIM. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">This is captured in the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">data set out </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">para</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">graphs</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">13</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">14</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">below. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Neither the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">FCA </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">nor the FSA before it </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">has sought to use </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">variations to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the primary markets regime </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to attract extractive companies</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> compared to companies more generally</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> to UK markets</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Would increased regulation for London listed extractives companies result in competition from elsewhere or can it be used to make the UK a centre of excellence for best</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> practice and corporate governance?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The FCA believes that</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">well-designed regulation, proportionate and relevant to the specific</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">concerns</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">it seeks to address,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">can make</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">financial centre</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a more</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">attractive</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">proposition</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to both investors and issuers,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">thereby</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">eepening</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the pool of investible capital.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Poorly designed</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">regulation, particularly regulation which is unclear, difficult to comply with, or which imposes</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">disproportionate</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">burdens on issuers</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is likely to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">have the opposite effect.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Similarly, we believe red</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ucing the burden of regulation without careful consideration will not necessarily make a financial centre more attractive as it may undermine confidence. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The FCA</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">will continue</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">refine and develop the listing regime in order </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">keep</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> it</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">abreast of developm</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ents, as the FSA </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">aimed to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">FCA policy initiatives are required to go through a consultation process and are subject to rigorous cost-benefit analysis disciplines.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The FCA's rules are focussed on the regulation of capital raising and the orderliness of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ongoing trading.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Extractive industry companies do of course operate within a much broader context of legislation and regulation, including company law and criminal law more generally. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We have a responsibility, as part of our objective of protecting and en</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">hancing the integrity of the UK financial system</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, to ensure the UK financial system is not used for a purpose connected with financial crime and is not affected by behaviour that amounts to market abuse.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">However, many concerns related to extractive indust</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ries do not fall under that objective.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">We are not the agency</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">best placed to address concerns</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">which ultimately amount to, for example, suspected fraud or corruption, or</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">issues related to broader development, environmental or human rights concerns.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Has the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> boom in London-listed extractive</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">companies with businesses overseas over the last two decades resulted in a strengthening in the UK’s competitive position in this sector?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Other respondents </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">may</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">be better placed to quantify the UK’s market share of the global extractive industries financing market and how it has changed over the last two decades, and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to say </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">whether that amounts to a strengthening of the UK’s competitive position. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">There clearly h</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">as been growth</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">in the last two decades. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">For example, the tables below shows</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">that this century the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">mining sector</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">on the London Stock Exchange’s Main Market</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">has more than doubled in value and was the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">four</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">largest sector on 31 July </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">2013. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">In the same month</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> in 2000 it was eighteenth. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Oil and gas shows less significant change over the same period.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Analysis of Main Market sector weightings, July 2013 v July 2000</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:21.3pt; width:610.4pt"><tr style="height:25.2pt"><td style="background-color:#fabf8f; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:44.65pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#fcd5b4; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td colspan="2" style="background-color:#fabf8f; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:81.55pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#ffffff; font-family